I apologize for the late response. I updated the docs following the suggestion by @Vtec234's suggestion.

I also added a note about what to do if proof term generation fails. The failure to generate proof terms occurs when using the normalization function in the string diagram widget. As a workaround we generate a meaningless term instead of generating an error.

Could you write an account somewhere of your plans with this (or point to existing Zulip discussion etc)?

I'm excited to have widget support for string diagrams, but I would like to know that
* this code will be maintainable into the future
* its learnt whatever lessons necessary from e.g. homotopy.io

and I think a bit more documentation would help produce this confidence!

@semorrison Thanks for the comment! I have added the note explaining the current situation and the future plan.

I've played a bit with homotopy.io before, but to be honest I don't know much about it (But now I should learn it).
